<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 04 at 8:46PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Macon,
southwestern Peach, south central Crawford and east central Taylor
Counties through 915 PM EDT...
At 846 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Saint Louis, or near
Fort Valley, moving west at 5 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.
Locations impacted include...
Fort Valley, Marshallville, Saint Louis, Lee Pope, Nakomis and
Winchester.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
